text_copy_copy.text:
Our name, Mānawa Bay, is inspired by our unique location here in the park-like grounds at the water's edge and the historical and cultural significance of this area to tangata whenua.

 

In te reo Māori, Mānawa means mangroves – a coastal plant species that provides a habitat for native birds and fish. They are a vital part of the eco-system and have long featured in the waterways surrounding the land Auckland Airport sits on. We acknowledge this in our name.
Mānawa Bay is committed to a number of key sustainability initiatives.

text_copy_copy_copy.text: Including; optimising resources, reducing carbon emissions, supporting local communities and enhancing our environment.
